HEADWORD: Mongolians
<hw>Mon*go"li*ans</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>One of
the great races of man, including the greater part of the inhabitants of
China, Japan, and the interior of Asia, with branches in Northern Europe
and other parts of the world. By some American Indians are considered a
branch of the Mongols. In a more restricted sense, the inhabitants of
Mongolia and adjacent countries, including the Burats and the
Kalmuks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

